==分类==
角蟾属分类存在争议。一种意见认为[[无耳蟾属|无耳蟾属]](''Atympanophrys'')、[[短腿蟾属|短腿蟾属]](''Brachytarsophrys'')、[[拟角蟾属|拟角蟾属]](''Ophryophryne'')、[[泛角蟾属|泛角蟾属]](''Panophrys'')及[[异角蟾属|异角蟾属]](''Xenophrys'')都应视为角蟾属的同物[[异名|异名]]<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kai |first1=Wang |last2=Jinlong |first2=Ren |last3=Hongman |first3=Chen |last4=Zhitong |first4=Lyu |last5=Xianguang |first5=Guo |last6=Ke |first6=Jiang |last7=Jinmin |first7=Chen |last8=Jiatang |first8=Li |last9=Peng |first9=Guo |last10=Yingyong |first10=Wang |last11=Jing |first11=Che |title=The updated checklists of amphibians and reptiles of China |journal=Biodiversity Science |date=2020-02-20 |volume=28 |issue=2 |pages=189 |doi=10.17520/biods.2019238}}</ref>。

2017年以后的多项研究都对角蟾属提出了不同的分类方案，一种是分为短腿蟾属、拟角蟾属、无耳蟾属、异角蟾属，同时将角蟾属限定于[[巽他古陆|巽他古陆]]，[[婆罗蟾属|婆罗蟾属]]则作为角蟾属的异名<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Chen |first1=Jin-Min |last2=Poyarkov |first2=Nikolay A. |last3=Suwannapoom |first3=Chatmongkon |last4=Lathrop |first4=Amy |last5=Wu |first5=Yun-He |last6=Zhou |first6=Wei-Wei |last7=Yuan |first7=Zhi-Yong |last8=Jin |first8=Jie-Qiong |last9=Chen |first9=Hong-Man |last10=Liu |first10=He-Qun |last11=Nguyen |first11=Truong Quang |last12=Nguyen |first12=Sang Ngoc |last13=Duong |first13=Tang Van |last14=Eto |first14=Koshiro |last15=Nishikawa |first15=Kanto |last16=Matsui |first16=Masafumi |last17=Orlov |first17=Nikolai L. |last18=Stuart |first18=Bryan L. |last19=Brown |first19=Rafe M. |last20=Rowley |first20=Jodi J.L. |last21=Murphy |first21=Robert W. |last22=Wang |first22=Ying-Yong |last23=Che |first23=Jing |title=Large-scale phylogenetic analyses provide insights into unrecognized diversity and historical biogeography of Asian leaf-litter frogs, genus Leptolalax (Anura: Megophryidae) |journal=Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution |date=2018-07 |volume=124 |pages=162–171 |doi=10.1016/j.ympev.2018.02.020}}</ref>；另一种意见则将拟角蟾属、无耳蟾属、短腿蟾属、泛角蟾属和异角蟾属均降为亚属、并视为角蟾属的同物异名<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Mahony |first1=Stephen |last2=Foley |first2=Nicole M. |last3=Biju |first3=S.D. |last4=Teeling |first4=Emma C. |title=Evolutionary History of the Asian Horned Frogs (Megophryinae): Integrative Approaches to Timetree Dating in the Absence of a Fossil Record |journal=Molecular Biology and Evolution |date=2017-01-18 |pages=msw267 |doi=10.1093/molbev/msw267}}</ref>。

